Tanzania to Screen Seven Companies for Oil Tender, Guardian Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-09-13T09:13:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/tanzania-to-screen-seven-companies-for-oil-tender-guardian-says.html
The Tanzania Petroleum Development
Corp. selected seven companies to be screened for a tender to
supply fuel to the country, the Dar es Salaam-based Guardian
reported, citing Tender Board Chairman Dismas Fuko.  The Commercial Petroleum Co. of Tanzania will be supplied
fuel by the winner of the tender, the newspaper said. The
companies to be screened include  Independent Petroleum Group (IPG) ,
Prevail Technologies Tanzania Ltd., Galana Petroleum Ltd.,
Trafigura PTE Ltd., Vitol SA, Augusta Energy SA and Addax Energy
SA, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam via Nairobi at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 